    "title": {
      "rendered": "15 Must-Know Fundraising and Social Media Stats"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-17362\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"Must Know Stats\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Must-Know-Stats.jpg?w=450&amp;ssl=1 450w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>LinkedIn launched in 2003, Facebook launched in 2004, and Twitter launched in 2006. Now more than a decade into the Social Web, the use of social networks\u00a0still continues to grow worldwide and <a href=\"http://www.statista.com/statistics/278414/number-of-worldwide-social-network-users/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>will continue to do so for\u00a0years to come</strong></a>. It&#8217;s no coincidence that online giving is growing rapidly as well. A decade ago\u00a0most individuals still consumed print news and donated by\u00a0<em>writing and mailing checks</em>. Today, as donors, activists, and volunteers worldwide have embraced the Internet for news and entertainment, so have they transitioned their giving and their trust to digital. The investment the early adopter nonprofits made into online fundraising technology and strategy in the late 1990&#8217;s and 2000&#8217;s\u00a0is now finally starting pay off<span style=\"color: #383838;\">\u00a0\u2013</span>\u00a0especially if they have also <strong><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">invested into a smart, multichannel, integrated social media strategy</a></strong>.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. #GivingTuesday 2014 raised 63% more than\u00a02013.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://casefoundation.org/blog/givingtuesday-moves-campaign-tradition/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17131\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/GivingTuesday.png?resize=600%2C502\" alt=\"GivingTuesday\" width=\"600\" height=\"502\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/GivingTuesday.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/GivingTuesday.png?resize=300%2C251&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://casefoundation.org/blog/givingtuesday-moves-campaign-tradition/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source: The Case Foundation</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Donors are\u00a034% more likely to give on responsive websites.</span></h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><a href=\"http://www.frogloop.com/care2blog/2014/12/10/do-responsive-websites-raise-more-money.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17255\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Responsive-Design.png?resize=600%2C399\" alt=\"Responsive Design\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Responsive-Design.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Responsive-Design.png?resize=300%2C199&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.frogloop.com/care2blog/2014/12/10/do-responsive-websites-raise-more-money.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source: Frogloop</strong></a><br />\n</span></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Email fundraising accounts in 1/3 of all revenue raised online.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/echoandcompany/photos/pb.14258025401.-2207520000.1420659533./10154543947055402/?type=3&amp;theater\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17306\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/email-fundraising.jpg?resize=600%2C408\" alt=\"email fundraising\" width=\"600\" height=\"408\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/email-fundraising.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/email-fundraising.jpg?resize=300%2C204&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/echoandcompany/photos/pb.14258025401.-2207520000.1420659533./10154543947055402/?type=3&amp;theater\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Echo &amp; Co.</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">4. 18% of Americans says supporting youth and family causes\u00a0are most important.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.harrisinteractive.com/NewsRoom/HarrisPolls/tabid/447/mid/1508/articleId/1481/ctl/ReadCustom%20Default/Default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17137\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/chartoftheday_2962_Charitable_Causes_Americans_Care_About_Most_n.jpg?resize=600%2C428\" alt=\"chartoftheday_2962_Charitable_Causes_Americans_Care_About_Most_n\" width=\"600\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/chartoftheday_2962_Charitable_Causes_Americans_Care_About_Most_n.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/chartoftheday_2962_Charitable_Causes_Americans_Care_About_Most_n.jpg?resize=300%2C214&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.harrisinteractive.com/NewsRoom/HarrisPolls/tabid/447/mid/1508/articleId/1481/ctl/ReadCustom%20Default/Default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source:\u00a0Harris Poll</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">5. 60% of millennials donate an average of $481 to nonprofits each year.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.happify.com/hd/science-of-giving-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17146\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Millennial-Giving.jpg?resize=600%2C347\" alt=\"Millennial Giving\" width=\"600\" height=\"347\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Millennial-Giving.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Millennial-Giving.jpg?resize=300%2C173&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.happify.com/hd/science-of-giving-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source: Happify</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">6. Online donors aged 55-64 are the most generous crowdfunders.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/kimbiainc/gla-infographicfinal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17142\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Crowdfunding-donors.jpg?resize=600%2C455\" alt=\"Crowdfunding donors\" width=\"600\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Crowdfunding-donors.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Crowdfunding-donors.jpg?resize=300%2C227&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/kimbiainc/gla-infographicfinal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source: Kimbia</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">7. Individual that earn $25,000US or less donate the largest share of their income to charity.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/katiasavchuk/2014/10/06/wealthy-americans-are-giving-less-of-their-incomes-to-charity-while-poor-are-donating-more/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17334\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/change-income-bracket-page-0011.jpg?resize=600%2C357\" alt=\"change-income-bracket-page-0011\" width=\"600\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/change-income-bracket-page-0011.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/change-income-bracket-page-0011.jpg?resize=300%2C178&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/katiasavchuk/2014/10/06/wealthy-americans-are-giving-less-of-their-incomes-to-charity-while-poor-are-donating-more/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source:\u00a0Chronicle of Philanthropy</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">8. PayPal mobile donations on Giving Tuesday 2014 increased 101% over 2013 in the United States and Canada.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.paypal-community.com/t5/PayPal-Forward/Give-Cheer-We-ll-Add-1-to-Your-Donation/ba-p/912515\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17144\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/paypal-mobile-donations.jpg?resize=600%2C424\" alt=\"paypal mobile donations\" width=\"600\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/paypal-mobile-donations.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/paypal-mobile-donations.jpg?resize=300%2C212&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>Source: PayPal</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">9. 19.8% of nonprofit event registrations occur on mobile devices.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://npengage.com/nonprofit-fundraising/5-myths-of-mobile-fundraising-debunked-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17331\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/EVENTS.png?resize=600%2C492\" alt=\"EVENTS\" width=\"600\" height=\"492\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/EVENTS.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/EVENTS.png?resize=300%2C246&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://npengage.com/nonprofit-fundraising/5-myths-of-mobile-fundraising-debunked-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: npENGAGE</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">10. May 6, 2014 was the largest single day of giving in U.S. history.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.kimbia.com/infographic-give-local-america-2014-results/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17139\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Give-Local-America-Infographic-2014.jpg?resize=600%2C402\" alt=\"Give Local America Infographic 2014\" width=\"600\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Give-Local-America-Infographic-2014.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Give-Local-America-Infographic-2014.jpg?resize=300%2C201&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.kimbia.com/infographic-give-local-america-2014-results/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source: Kimbia</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">11. Myanmar, also known as Burma, is the most charitable nation.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.cafamerica.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17149\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/myanmar.jpg?resize=600%2C428\" alt=\"myanmar\" width=\"600\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/myanmar.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/myanmar.jpg?resize=300%2C214&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.cafamerica.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source: CAF America</strong></a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">12. Facebook, LinkedIn, and Pinterest are the most regularly accessed networks.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.emarketer.com/article.aspx?R=1011592\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17151\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/most-popular-social-networks-with-adults.png?resize=600%2C424\" alt=\"most popular social networks with adults\" width=\"600\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/most-popular-social-networks-with-adults.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/most-popular-social-networks-with-adults.png?resize=300%2C212&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.emarketer.com/article.aspx?R=1011592\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Cowen and Company</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">13. Facebook, Tumblr, and Instagram are where users spend the most time.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.emarketer.com/article.aspx?R=1011592\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17152\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/popular-social-networks-with-young-people.png?resize=600%2C368\" alt=\"popular social networks with young people\" width=\"600\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/popular-social-networks-with-young-people.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/popular-social-networks-with-young-people.png?resize=300%2C184&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.emarketer.com/article.aspx?R=1011592\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Cowen and Company</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">14. East Asia constitutes a staggering 33% of all active social media accounts worldwide.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://wearesocial.sg/blog/2015/01/digital-social-mobile-2015/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17353\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/global-social-media-users.png?resize=600%2C445\" alt=\"global social media users\" width=\"600\" height=\"445\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/global-social-media-users.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/global-social-media-users.png?resize=300%2C222&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://wearesocial.sg/blog/2015/01/digital-social-mobile-2015/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: We Are Social</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">15. The average salary in the United States for a mid-career social media manager is $56,218.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.payscale.com/research/US/Job=Social_Media_Manager/Salary/04d50703/Mid-Career\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17355\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/nonprofit-social-media-salary.png?resize=600%2C413\" alt=\"nonprofit social media salary\" width=\"600\" height=\"413\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/nonprofit-social-media-salary.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/nonprofit-social-media-salary.png?resize=300%2C206&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.payscale.com/research/US/Job=Social_Media_Manager/Salary/04d50703/Mid-Career\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: PayScale</a></h3>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
